      "message": "Is this right? This unconditionally declares a C++ struct AHardwareBuffer for everyone who includes this file, including Chrome code built without NDK platform level 26 support, but the actual declaration in the NDK header is:\n\nextern \"C\" {\ntypedef struct AHardwareBuffer AHardwareBuffer;\n}\n\nAs far as I know this isn\u0027t fully equivalent, for example callers in another namespace would have to use \"::AHardwareBuffer\" for the C++ struct vs unprefixed \"AHardwareBuffer\" for the extern \"C\" struct.\n\nI\u0027m working on changes that will add AHardwareBuffer-related methods to Chrome and that will use the \"C\" definition, and want to make sure that we won\u0027t get conflicts for code that includes both. See for example: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/679961/7/ui/gl/gl_bindings.h",
